raw_data.title: INSTR2-H/Instructor II (Hourly)
raw_data.description: (Assistant Project Manager) – In addition to the Instructor I requirements, the Instructor II has in-depth knowledge and at least three (3) years of experience in a field directly related to the training. raw_data.title: INSTR3-H/Instructor III (Hourly)
raw_data.description: (Project Manager) – In addition to the qualifications of Instructor II, this person possesses an advanced knowledge or at least five (5) years of professional experience in a field directly related to the training.  This position may also be utilized for project managers, assistant project managers, weapons handlers, and may oversee Cut Suit Subject Matter Experts.  The individual will be responsible for planning and coordinating the training exercise based on the unit training schedule and operational requirements.  This person identifies the role-player and instruction support, the special effects, vehicles, and locations to be used.  The position advises the unit trainers in the best methods to coordinate the special effects and role-players into scenarios to achieve the training objectives.
